{"questionId":"5203","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Organic compounds often have isomers.</p>\n<p>A straight chain molecule of formula C<sub>5</sub>H<sub>10</sub>O contains a carbonyl group. The compound&nbsp;cannot be oxidized by acidified potassium dichromate(VI) solution.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Deduce the structural formulas of the two possible isomers.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4534/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-08_om_16.55.28.png\" alt=\"M18/4/CHEMI/HP2/ENG/TZ2/09.a.i/M\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept condensed formulas.</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"5203","referenceCode":"18M.2.hl.TZ2.9a.i","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Deduce the structural formulas of the two possible isomers.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.1 Fundamentals of organic chemistry","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}